text: What could you tempt me with? Bretonnian - your fey, weak, water sprite doesn’t scare me.
With what do you bargain, mortal?
Coward! You come before me pleading a pact we have no need for - for us, there is just death.
The Dark Gods look down on your offer with interest, as do the Kurgans.
You seek the Kurgan: I am their shaman, their mage… their sorcerer. They follow my whim…
Agreed, but the tribes never forget an insult!
A weakling and a fool, that is what I see before me. Go and tell your masters the Kurgans come for you all!
I speak for the Kurgan tribes, and we deny your petty offer.
